IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDescription: THE NOT FOR PROFIT CORPORATION WAS ORGANIZED TO OWN AND OPERATE A 41 UNIT APARTMENT COMMUNITY IN GARNER, NORTH CAROLINA KNOWN AS CHADWICK APARTMENTS. IT WAS ORGANIZED PURSUANT TO SECTION 202 OF THE NATIONAL HOUSING ACT AS AMENDED AND HAS ENTERED INTO THE STANDARD FHA REGULATORY AGREEMENTS, WHICH GOVERN THE OPERATION OF THE COMMUNITY, WITH THE FEDERAL HOUSING ADMINISTRATION SECTION OF HUD. A PROJECT RENTAL ASSISTANCE CONTRACT (PRAC) PROVIDES RENT ASSISTANCE FOR LOW INCOME FAMILIES (OR PERSONS).

Form990ScheduleDPartXIV.ReturnReference: Description of Uncertain Tax Positions Under FIN 48:
Form990ScheduleDPartXIV.Explanation: In 2009, the Corporation adopted the Income Taxes topic of the FASB Accounting Standards Codification (ASC) 740, which provides guidance for how uncertain income tax positions should be recognized, measured, presented and disclosed in the financial statements. The Corporation is required to evaluate the income tax positions taken or expected to be taken to determine whether the positions are "more-likely-than-not" to be sustained upon examination by the applicable tax authority. The Corporation has determined that the application of the Income Taxes standard does not impact the operations of the Corporation and that no provision for income tax is required in the Corporation's financial statements. There has been no interest or penalties recognized in the income statement or balance sheet for the years ended May 31, 2010 and 2009. As of May 31, 2010 and 2009, the following federal and state tax years remain open - United States: years ended May 31, 2010, 2009, 2008 and 2007, and State of Indiana: years ended May 31, 2010, 2009, 2008 and 2007.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section A, line 3
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: CHADWICK APARTMENTS, INC. IS MANAGED BY COMMUNITY MANAGEMENT CORPORATION, A PROFESSIONAL PROPERTY MANAGEMENT COMPANY. COMMUNITY MANAGEMENT CORPORATION HAS A PROJECT OWNER'S & MANAGEMENT AGENT'S CERTIFICATION FOR MULTIFAMILY HOUSING PROJECTS WITH THE US DEPARTMENT OF HOUSING AND URBAN DEVELOPMENT. UNDER THIS CERTIFICATION HUD HAS APPROVED COMMUNITY MANAGEMENT CORPORATION TO MANAGE THE CHADWICK APARTMENTS ELDERLY HOUSING PROPERTY.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section A, line 7a
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: The Board of DHIC has the ability to elect one or more of the board members of the organization.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, line 11
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: THE AUDITING FIRM SENDS A DRAFT OF THE RETURN TO DHIC. DHIC FORWARDS A COPY OF THE RETURN TO EACH BOARD MEMBER FOR THEIR COMMENTS PRIOR TO FILING.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, line 12c
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: BOARD MEMBERS AND OFFICERS MUST SIGN THE POLICY ANNUALLY. THE POLICY IS REVIEWED ANNUALLY AT BOARD MEETINGS.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, line 15
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: The organization's officers are paid thru DHIC which has its own compensation policies.

GeneralExplanation.Identifier: Form 990, Part VI, Section C, line 19
GeneralExplanation.Explanation: THE FORM 990 AND ALL RELATED FINANCIAL AND POLICY INFORMATION ARE MADE AVAILABLE TO THE PUBLIC UPON WRITTEN REQUEST AS WELL AS ON GUIDESTAR.ORG. GOVERNING DOCUMENTS, CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICIES AND FINANCIALS ARE ALSO AVAILABLE UPON REQUEST.

THE MANAGEMENT COMPANY and DHIC RECEIVES A COPY OF THE AUDIT. PRIOR TO THE FINALIZATION OF THE AUDIT, A COPY OF THE AUDIT IS GIVEN TO ALL OF THE BOARD MEMBERS FOR THEIR COMMENTS. WHEN THE AUDIT IS UP FOR BID, THE BOARD DISCUSSES THE RELATIONSHIP WITH THE CURRENT AUDITORS AND MAKES A DETERMINATION AS TO WHETHER TO MAINTAIN THIS RELATIONSHIP OR CHANGE TO A NEW AUDITING FIRM.
DHIC employs the officers of the project. There is no reimbursement paid to DHIC.
